headline_main: Which 2020 Democrats Raised the Most Money This Summer?

abstract: Mr. Booker raised $6 million in the past three months, and he met a $1.7 million goal over 10 days that he said was needed to keep his campaign alive.
snippet: Mr. Booker raised $6 million in the past three months, and he met a $1.7 million goal over 10 days that he said was needed to keep his campaign alive.
lead_paragraph: Senator Cory Booker of New Jersey raised more than $6 million in the past three months, his campaign said on Tuesday, his best fund-raising quarter yet but one that still falls short of the leading candidates’ hauls.

abstract: Pierre-Olivier Bouée has resigned after revelations that the Swiss bank had snooped on a former executive. But Credit Suisse’s C.E.O. was found not to be involved.

abstract: The large total for his 2020 presidential bid reflected the senator’s continued strength with small-dollar donors.
snippet: The large total for his 2020 presidential bid reflected the senator’s continued strength with small-dollar donors.
lead_paragraph: Senator Bernie Sanders raised $25.3 million in the past three months, his campaign said on Tuesday, a total that continues to demonstrate his strength with small donors as he fights to maintain support in key early-voting states.

headline_main: Bernie Sanders’s Fund-Raising Haul: $25.3 Million in Third Quarter

abstract: The amount is less than what he raised during the previous quarter, when he topped the field in fund-raising with almost $25 million in donations.
snippet: The amount is less than what he raised during the previous quarter, when he topped the field in fund-raising with almost $25 million in donations.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Mayor Pete Buttigieg of South Bend, Ind., raised $19.1 million for his presidential campaign during the last three months, his campaign said Tuesday. The figure represents a decrease in his fund-raising pace from earlier in the summer.

headline_main: Hong Kong, Alberto Salazar, Jessye Norman: Your Tuesday Briefing

abstract: Proposals from Elizabeth Warren and Bernie Sanders have raised concerns from economists and business leaders who fear the plans would sap economic growth.
snippet: Proposals from Elizabeth Warren and Bernie Sanders have raised concerns from economists and business leaders who fear the plans would sap economic growth.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Progressive Democrats are advocating the most drastic shift in tax policy in over a century as they look to redistribute wealth and chip away at the economic power of the superrich with new taxes that could fundamentally reshape the United States economy.

abstract: Democrats have moved left, but the party’s rank and file typically side with establishment favorites.
snippet: Democrats have moved left, but the party’s rank and file typically side with establishment favorites.
lead_paragraph: Elizabeth Warren is gaining. She has breached 20 percent of the vote in recent national surveys and might hold a narrow lead in Iowa and New Hampshire. The prediction markets now consider her a clear favorite to win the nomination. It can be hard to see how her Democratic rivals will attack or stop her.

headline_main: Send Us Your Money or the Kitten Gets It

abstract: Why do they hate her? It’s mainly about their egos.
snippet: Why do they hate her? It’s mainly about their egos.
lead_paragraph: Remember when pundits used to argue that Elizabeth Warren wasn’t likable enough to be president? It was always a lazy take, with a strong element of sexism. And it looks ridiculous now, watching Warren on the campaign trail. Never mind whether she’s someone you’d like to have a beer with, she’s definitely someone thousands of people want to take selfies with.
